    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Creeping species with underground runners rooted at the nodes and sending up short vertical stems that usually arise in pairs from the nodes and are covered by plump, barrel-shaped segments 7-15 mm long and 2-5 mm wide. The tiny white flowers are arranged in threes on the distal segments. Colour can be transparent light green, but often reddish.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9771",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Typically reach a height of only about 20 cm, segments 2-5 mm wide.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9772",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to southern Africa, extending from Namibia to Mozambique.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> In estuaries and salt-water lagoons along entire coast of South Africa.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9773",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Salt-tolerant plant that occurs low on sandy and muddy shores in both estuaries and fully-marine saltmarshes<i>, </i>where regularly inundated by the tide. Often forms dense beds such as in Geelbek, Langebaan.</p><p>Species in this genus have a long history of use as food plants in Europe and can be eaten raw in salads, pickled, or cooked as a vegetable.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9774",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9775",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Members of this genus are typically wind pollinated and produce small seeds which are dispersed by wind or water. This species flowers from November to June with a peak in December and seed production peaks in February.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9776",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The most abundant of several other similar species found in the region. Detailed examination is required to distinguish these â€“ see references provided.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9777",
            "longText": null,
